1lw.title: Mathematics
1lw.clickbait: Mathematics is the study of numbers and other ideal objects that can be described by axioms.
1lw.text:
Mathematics is the study of crisply specified formal objects - for example, numbers - and the ways of knowing their properties - such as proofs.  Defining logic as the study of which conclusions follow with certainty from which premises, we can also see mathematics as the study of logical objects in logical universes - those things whose properties follow from specifications about them, rather than from observation of the real world.

Arbital is not presently embarking on the project of explaining all of mathematics, so the main pages here should be math topics and requisites that are required by other Arbital pages.
